<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;E holy Rode, &thorn;e swete treo&middot; riht is to hauen in muynde,<MILESTONE N="28b:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;at ha&thorn; from strong de&thorn; i-brouht&middot; to lyue al Monkuynde,</L>
<L>&THORN;orwh a treo we weore for-lore&middot; and furst i-brouht to grounde,</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;orwh a treo se&thorn;&thorn;e to liue i-brou&yogh;t&middot; I-heried beo &thorn;ulke stounde!</L>
<L>Al hit com of one More&middot; &thorn;at vs to de&thorn;e brou&yogh;te,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at vs&middot; to lyue a&yogh;ein&middot; &thorn;orwh Ihesus &thorn;at vs bou&yogh;te;</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e treo&middot; &thorn;at vre furste Fader&middot; &thorn;e lu&thorn;er Appel of nom&middot;,</L>
<L N="8">In &thorn;e Maner&middot; &thorn;at ich ow telle wole&middot; &thorn;e swete Rode com:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;o Adam vre furste Fader&middot; &thorn;e sunne hedde i-do</L>
<L>And i-driue out of Paradis&middot;, and his wyf also,</L>
<L>After Milce wel &yogh;eorne he criede&middot;, &thorn;ei&yogh; hit late were;</L>
<L N="12">A bi-heste he hedde of vr lord&middot;, &thorn;o me him drof out &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>&THORN;at whon &thorn;e tyme weore folfuld&middot; vr lord him wolde bi|&thorn;enche,</L>
<L>And mid Oyle of merci smere him&middot; and his sunnes quenche:</L>
<L>Gret hope hedde Adam&middot; to &thorn;is bi-heste euer-mo:</L>
<L N="16">In &thorn;e valeye of Ebron&middot; he liuede mid teone and wo:</L>
<L>Twey soncs he hedde se&thorn;&thorn;e&middot;, Caym&middot; and Abel:</L>
<L>For Envye&middot; &thorn;at on slou&yogh; &thorn;at o&thorn;ur&middot;, And &thorn;at &yogh;e wite&thorn; wel:
<PB REF="00000053.tif" N="21"></L>
<L>&THORN;o Caym hedde his bro&thorn;ur i-slawe&middot; i-flemed he was &thorn;er|fore:</L>
<L N="20">&THORN;o Adam say&yogh; &thorn;at he hedde&middot; bo&thorn;e his sones for-lore</L>
<L>He wep and made deol i-nouh&middot;: "lord," he seide "&thorn;in ore!</L>
<L>Neih wommon ichaue to muche i-beo&middot;, I nule come neih hire no more!</L>
<L>&THORN;reo harmes ichabbe for hire i-had&middot;, my self furst for|lore,</L>
<L N="24">And nou my sones, welawey!&middot; of Al. wommon is more":</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;o nolde Adam come neih his wyf&middot; two hundred &yogh;er and more,</L>
<L>For wo &thorn;at he hedde i-had&middot;, and euere he lyuede in sore:</L>
<L>From vr lord toknynge he hedde se&thorn;&thorn;e&middot; &thorn;at he scholde to his wyf wende:</L>
<L N="28">Ne dorste he not beo &thorn;er a-&yogh;eyn&middot;: A child he hedde atte ende,</L>
<L>Seth; he let his nome nempne&middot;, and se&thorn;&thorn;en heo hedden mo:</L>
<L>Al his lyf &thorn;is seli mon&middot; liuede in teone and wo:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;o he was of Nyne hundred &yogh;er&middot;, and two and &thorn;ritti old,</L>
<L N="32">His streng&thorn;e faylede of his Limes&middot;, his bodi bi-com al cold;</L>
