<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="legend"><PB REF="00000139.tif" N="107">

<PB REF="00000140.tif" N="[108]">
<HEAD>VI.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="version">
<HEAD>HOW &THORN;E HALI CROS WAS FUNDIN. BE SEINT<LB>ELAINE<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Fairfax MS. 14, Bod. Lib.<MILESTONE N="88b" UNIT="folio">, art, 63.]</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Of &thorn;e rode now for to rede</L>
<L>ihesus criste he be mi spede,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;are-on suffred sorouful pine</L>
<L N="4">to lause vs fra our wi&thorn;er-wine;</L>
<L>we agh to buxumli hit bere,</L>
<L>for hit of bote is our banere,</L>
<L>ba&thorn; on bodi and in hert,</L>
<L N="8">againe alle our care hit is our quert.</L>
<L>quen ihesus &thorn;er-of was vn-done,</L>
<L>&thorn;e iewes hid hit efter sone</L>
<L>fra cristen men hit to blinde;</L>
<L N="12">la&thorn; ware ham &thorn;ai sulde hit finde,</L>
<L>&thorn;ai wiste &thorn;e cristen walde hit kepe</L>
<L>for-&thorn;i in er&thorn; &thorn;ai grofe hit depe</L>
<L>vnder er&thorn;, and o&thorn;er twa</L>
<L N="16">quare-on &thorn;e theuis hang on squa;</L>
<L>&thorn;e ri&yogh;t rode &thorn;ai went to dille</L>
<L>out of &thorn;e cristen mennis skille,</L>
<L>&thorn;at if wi&thorn; chaunce men on ham hit</L>
<L N="20">quilk &thorn;ai sulde haue &thorn;ai sulde no&yogh;t witt:</L>
<L>&para; bot crist, &thorn;at nane is to him like,</L>
<L>walde no&yogh;t late his dere relike,</L>
<L>squa noteful &thorn;ing, squa lang be hid,</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;at he ne walde &thorn;at hit ware kid.</L>
<L>quen hit had bene ij. hundre &yogh;ere</L>
<L>vnder er&thorn;, &thorn;at druri dere,</L>
<L>to bote of ba&thorn; our saule and life,</L>
<L N="28">he did hit be fundin &thorn;orou a wife:
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="109"></L>
<L>a du&yogh;ti wife, &thorn;at hi&yogh;t Eline,</L>
<L>was moder of king costantine,</L>
<L>ho fande hit, qua-sum wil wite hit now,</L>
<L N="32">herkin and I sal tel hit &yogh;ou.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Als in stori. I. red and fande,</L>
<L>quen costantine was liuande</L>
<L>of rome &thorn;en was he emperour,</L>
<L N="36">againe he&thorn;in folk sti&thorn;e in stoure;</L>
<L>be-tid a tide &thorn;at he&thorn;in lede</L>
<L>come him batail for to bede;</L>
<L>sa mikil folk &thorn;ai wi&thorn; ham led</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;at costantine was sare a-dred.</L>
<L>&thorn;ai come tille him &thorn;at ilk ni&yogh;t</L>
<L>atte &thorn;ai sulde on &thorn;e morne fi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&para; A man &thorn;at selcou&thorn; faire was graide<MILESTONE N="89" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="44">come to &thorn;e kinge and &thorn;us he saide:&mdash;</L>
<L>"costantine loke vp and se</L>
<L>til heiuen-warde and conforte &thorn;e."</L>
<L>he lokid vp and in &thorn;at si&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="48">he sagh [&thorn;ar] cristis crosse ful bri&yogh;t;</L>
<L>a titel sagh he &thorn;ar-on lye,</L>
<L>"here-in &thorn;ou salle haue victorie."</L>
<L>&thorn;en did &thorn;e kinge make [of] a neyuen<NOTE PLACE="marg">read <I>an euen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">suche a cros as he sagh in heyuen<NOTE PLACE="marg">read <I>heuen</I>.</NOTE>;</L>
<L>and vp in trau&thorn; he ras stedefast</L>
<L>and bra&thorn;eli on his faas he brast,</L>
<L>and did &thorn;at cros be-for him lede</L>
<L N="56">and felled doun &thorn;at cursid lede;</L>
<L>&thorn;ai felle, &thorn;ai fled &thorn;a wi&thorn;er-wine,</L>
<L>&thorn;e victorie has kinge costantine</L>
<L>&thorn;orou &thorn;e croice and cristis mi&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="60">and &thorn;orou &thorn;aire stedfast trau&thorn; in [d]ri&yogh;t.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;en sende &thorn;e king constantine</L>
<L>sandis til his moder eline</L>
<L>for to do seche, wi&thorn;-outen hone,</L>
<L N="64">&thorn;e cros &thorn;at criste on was done,
<PB REF="00000142.tif" N="110"></L>
<L>to finde &thorn;at hali tree sum-quare</L>
<L>and make a kirke be raisid &thorn;are.</L>
<L>benciras and ansiers,</L>
<L N="68">&thorn;er twa men was messagers,</L>
<L>&thorn;ai ware sende to &thorn;e quene fra rome;</L>
<L>bot herkenis how &thorn;ai gaue dome.</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;is lauedi had &thorn;en hir wi&thorn;</L>
<L N="72">a cristen man, was gode goldsmi&thorn;,</L>
<L>quat &thorn;ing &thorn;at ho him of walde mou&thorn;[e]</L>
<L>atte hir deuise make he cou&thorn;e,</L>
<L>bot pouer he was of litil a&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="76">and to a iew mikil he a&yogh;t</L>
<L>a soumme of money for to amount,</L>
<L>and askid him ful harde a-count;</L>
<L>&thorn;e couenand was made ful harde</L>
<L N="80">and saide he made him suche forwarde,</L>
<L>if he his money mu&yogh;t no&yogh;t gett,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he sulde &yogh;ilde him for his dett</L>
<L>&thorn;at ilk we&yogh;t at &thorn;er was lesse</L>
<L N="84">he sulde &yogh;ilde of his awen flesse.</L>
<L>&thorn;e dai Is past, &thorn;e dette vn-quit,</L>
<L>&thorn;e bodi be-houis be-leue for hit.</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;e cristen dred ful sare &thorn;e pine,</L>
<L N="88">bot &thorn;e iew walde neuer fine.</L>
<L>ba&thorn; to &thorn;e quenis court &thorn;ai come,</L>
<L>&thorn;e iew &thorn;rali bad gif him dome.</L>
<L>sharp grundin knife in hande he bare,</L>
<L N="92">&thorn;e cristen<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. has <I>iew</I> altered to <I>cristen</I>.</NOTE> stode nakid be-for him &thorn;are;</L>
<L>&thorn;ai walde for money had him bo&yogh;t,</L>
<L>bot grante of &thorn;e iew gatte &thorn;ai no&yogh;t;</L>
<L>of raunsoun na mare &thorn;en a risshe</L>
<L N="96">walde he take bot of his flesshe.</L>
<L>&para; Saide benciras and ansiers:&mdash;</L>
<L>"&thorn;ou sal haue bro&thorn;er al &thorn;i fers,</L>
<L>&thorn;e quene has biddin vs to deme</L>
<L N="100">And al &thorn;at resoun is to queme,
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="111"></L>
<L>say vs how &thorn;ou wil him di&yogh;t</L>
<L>and we salle giue &thorn;e dome ful ri&yogh;t."</L>
<L>&para; "how," saide &thorn;e iew, "bot be my lay,</L>
<L N="104">&thorn;at werst &thorn;at euer I. can or may,</L>
<L>his eien first putt out I. sal</L>
<L>and his hende smite of wi&thorn;-al;</L>
<L>tonge and neise wil I. no&yogh;t saue,</L>
<L N="108">til atte I al my couenande haue."</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;e messagers him gaf ansquare</L>
<L>"&thorn;en semis hit no&yogh;t &thorn;ou wil him spare,</L>
<L>take &thorn;ou &thorn;e flesse we deme &thorn;e,</L>
<L N="112">squa atte &thorn;e blode mai sauid be;</L>
<L>a drope of blode if atte &thorn;ou tine</L>
<L>we gif &yogh;ou dome, &thorn;e wrange is &thorn;ine;</L>
<L>al if his flesshe was salde and bo&yogh;t</L>
<L N="116">his blode to selle neuer he &thorn;o&yogh;t;</L>
<L>&thorn;e fallis &thorn;e flesshe, we ar wele knawen,</L>
<L>kepe him &thorn;e blode &thorn;at is his awen."</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;en saide &thorn;at iew, "be saint dri&yogh;tine</L>
<L N="120">me &thorn;ink &thorn;e wers part is mine;</L>
<L>to take &thorn;e flesshe if I. assay</L>
<L>&thorn;en &thorn;e blode wil ryn a-way;</L>
<L>for-done &yogh;e haue me wi&thorn; &yogh;our dome,</L>
<L N="124">and &thorn;at make &yogh;e romains of rome;</L>
<L>maugrefe &thorn;er-fore mote &yogh;e haue,</L>
<L>alle &thorn;at suche a dome me gaue."</L>
<L>&para; benciras &thorn;en saide, "parfay</L>
<L N="128">alle has &thorn;is court herde &thorn;e missay,</L>
<L>me and my felaw sir ansiere;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou has missaide ri&yogh;t foule here,</L>
<L>we wil missay &thorn;e na wi&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="132">bot ellis of &thorn;e we wil haue ri&yogh;t;</L>
<L>&thorn;e lauedi, for ho did vs leue,</L>
<L>ho bad vs ri&yogh;tli dome to giue,</L>
<L>and &thorn;e so&thorn; we haue &thorn;e saide,</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;er-fore &thorn;ou dos vs now vpbraide."
<PB REF="00000144.tif" N="112"></L>
<L>&para; &thorn;e lauedi bad, wi&thorn;-outen lite,</L>
<L>iugement on him &thorn;ai sulde giue tite,</L>
<L>for sicure was ho &thorn;an of site,<MILESTONE N="89b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="140">&thorn;at &thorn;e cristen man was quite.</L>
<L>&thorn;e iew was dampned, so at &thorn;e quene</L>
<L>sulde al his catel haue be dene,</L>
<L>In hir merci his tonge to take,</L>
<L N="144">&thorn;at in hir presence suche wordis spake.</L>
<L>&thorn;e iew him &thorn;u&yogh;t selcou&thorn; tene</L>
<L>atte &thorn;is dome at was sa kene,</L>
<L>and saide on hi&yogh;t, atte al mu&yogh;t here,</L>
<L N="148">"me ware leuer &yogh;ou to lere</L>
<L>quare lijs &yogh;our lordis rode tree,</L>
<L>&thorn;en &thorn;us smartli dampned be."</L>
<L>&para; "god wate frende," &thorn;en saide eline,</L>
<L N="152">"&thorn;ou sal be quite of alle &thorn;i pine</L>
<L>if &thorn;ou wil do as I. &thorn;e bid,</L>
<L>to shew vs quere &thorn;at cros is hid."</L>
<L>"lauedi," he saide, "be my lay,</L>
<L N="156">&thorn;e so&thorn; &yogh;et can I. no&yogh;t say;</L>
<L>bot sette me a certaine day</L>
<L>&thorn;at wi&thorn; my maistris speke I may,</L>
<L>I salle &thorn;e bringe ti&thorn;ande of hit,</L>
<L N="160">&thorn;e quilk ble&thorn;eli &thorn;ou walde witt"</L>
<L>&para; "Gladli," ho saide, "here I &thorn;e hi&yogh;t</L>
<L>of a day respite and a ni&yogh;t;"</L>
<L>&para; saide elaine, "certis bot &thorn;ou hit finde</L>
<L N="164">of ba&thorn; &thorn;ine eien &thorn;ou sal be blinde."</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;e iew him sped tawarde his tide,</L>
<L>ouer his day durst he no&yogh;t bide;</L>
<L>na selcou&thorn; if he dred him sare,</L>
<L N="168">he wiste &thorn;e quene walde him no&yogh;t spare;</L>
<L>til hir he went better spede,</L>
<L>and saide, "lauedi I. knaw my dede,</L>
<L>priuely be-houis vs fare,</L>
<L N="172">and folowes me wi&thorn;-outen mare."
<PB REF="00000145.tif" N="113"></L>
<L>&thorn;ar-fore he went him sone in hy</L>
<L>vn-to &thorn;e mount of caluary;</L>
<L>and o&thorn;er folk went wi&thorn; &thorn;e quene,</L>
<L N="176">&thorn;idder &thorn;ai went al bedene.</L>
<L>&para; sone quen &thorn;ai &thorn;aire praier makid,</L>
<L>&thorn;e er&thorn; vnder ham hit shakid.</L>
<L>&thorn;en saide &thorn;e iew &thorn;at al &thorn;is herde,</L>
<L N="180">"criste &thorn;ou art sauiour of &thorn;is werde!"</L>
<L>his cla&thorn;is he kest, al bot his serke,</L>
<L>to make him nemil vn-to his werke;</L>
<L>si&thorn;en he toke a spade in hande,</L>
<L N="184">lange he dalue, bot no&yogh;t he fande;</L>
<L>&para; quen he ri&yogh;t depe had dellui[n] sare,</L>
<L>mare &thorn;en xx. fote or mare,</L>
<L>&thorn;ai fande iij. crossis; an was &thorn;at ilke,</L>
<L N="188">bot wiste &thorn;ai no&yogh;t quilk was quilk,</L>
<L>&thorn;e quilk mu&yogh;t be &thorn;e lordis tre,</L>
<L>and quilk mu&yogh;t &thorn;e theuis be:</L>
<L>wi&thorn; mikil ioy and mikil gle,</L>
<L N="192">to &thorn;e toun &thorn;ai bare &thorn;a &thorn;re;</L>
<L>&thorn;er ware &thorn;ai done in certaine place,</L>
<L>for to a-bide our lordis grace.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Aboute midward of &thorn;e day and mare</L>
<L N="196">a dede man cors for&thorn; &thorn;ai bare;</L>
<L>saint elaine made hir praier &thorn;are,</L>
<L>so did al &thorn;e folk was &thorn;are,</L>
<L>&thorn;at crist sulde ham takening shaw</L>
<L N="200">his awen dere tree to knaw.</L>
<L>on ai&thorn;er tree &thorn;e cors on rane,</L>
<L>bot alwais lay hit stil as stane;</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;e &thorn;rid &thorn;ai touchid wi&thorn; his hide,</L>
<L N="204">and vp he rase wi&thorn;-outen bide,</L>
<L>and spac wi&thorn; a bli&thorn; voyce,</L>
<L>and &thorn;us gatis he hailsed &thorn;e croice:&mdash;</L>
<L>"god loke &thorn;e cros precious &thorn;inge,</L>
<L N="208">on &thorn;e hange &thorn;at heiest kinge;
<PB REF="00000146.tif" N="114"></L>
<L>menskid wi&thorn; his flesshe was &thorn;ou,</L>
<L>of alle trees maste of vertu;</L>
<L>he has &thorn;e halghed at mast con ken,</L>
<L N="212">and &thorn;e salle mensk al cristen men."</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;is miracle sene wi&thorn; mani man,</L>
<L>&thorn;ai bare hit to &thorn;e temple &thorn;an;</L>
<L>&thorn;e Iewes to &thorn;e baptim ran,</L>
<L N="216">&thorn;er was cristened mani a man.</L>
<L>quen &thorn;at cros was bro&yogh;t in</L>
<L>men mu&yogh;t se &thorn;inge is &yogh;et to myn,</L>
<L>for &thorn;at tree &thorn;at hit of was shorne,</L>
<L N="220">as talde is in &thorn;is boke be-forne,</L>
<L>and al-wais in &thorn;at temple lay,</L>
<L>and &yogh;et was funden &thorn;er &thorn;at day;</L>
<L>hit &yogh;alde of hit sa squete a smel,</L>
<L N="224">how gode hit was can I. no&yogh;t tel;</L>
<L>&thorn;e smelle ouer al &thorn;e temple spred,</L>
<L><I>and &thorn;er</I>-wi&thorn; amendid ilka sted;</L>
<L>and bi &thorn;at smellinge mu&yogh;t man se</L>
<L N="228">hit was shorne of &thorn;at ilk tree.</L>
<L>&para; a iew &thorn;at mikil had herde and sene,</L>
<L>he talde &thorn;e so&thorn; vn-to &thorn;e quene,</L>
<L>and saide, his eldris talde him be dene,</L>
<L N="232">quatkin a tree hit sulde haue bene;</L>
<L>quen ho had herde al his resoun,</L>
<L>&thorn;en can ho make hir orisoun,</L>
<L>&thorn;at god witering sulde sende hir sone,<MILESTONE N="90" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="236">whar ho sulde &thorn;at cros done.</L>
<L>&para; our lorde hir sende an angel wise,</L>
<L>and bad hir dele hit in foure partise;</L>
<L>&thorn;e tane sulde in &thorn;e temple lende,</L>
<L N="240">to rome men sulde &thorn;e to&thorn;er sende,</L>
<L>til alisaundre to bere &thorn;e &thorn;rid,</L>
<L>&thorn;e fir&thorn; to bere hir Seluin mid,</L>
<L>to costentine with hir to wende,</L>
<L N="244">and alsqua did. &thorn;at lauedi hende.
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="115"></L>
<L>&para; In foure pecis &thorn;ai hit smate,</L>
<L>of &thorn;e quiche got hit wate;</L>
<L>&thorn;ai did ri&yogh;t with ij. as god ment,</L>
<L N="248">til rome and alisaundre ham sent;</L>
<L>&thorn;e &thorn;rid &thorn;ai left in &thorn;at cit&eacute;,</L>
<L>as in stede of auctorit&eacute;;</L>
<L>&thorn;e fir&thorn; led hir wi&thorn; eline</L>
<L N="252">vn-to hir sone king costantine;</L>
<L>to mete hir &yogh;ode mani baroun,</L>
<L>wi&thorn; grete and faire processioun;</L>
<L>wi&thorn;-in &thorn;e kirke of saint sophie</L>
<L N="256">&thorn;er haue &thorn;ai sette hit richelie;</L>
<L>was neuer &yogh;et na tree in lande</L>
<L>sa riche ne sa faire shewande;</L>
<L>Men was wonte to come to se</L>
<L N="260">at ilke paskis &thorn;at hali tree.</L>
<L>daies iiij. ham sette for stage</L>
<L>&thorn;e emperour wi&thorn; his baronage,</L>
<L>&para; a-pon &thorn;e day of mandee;</L>
<L N="264">&thorn;e riche quene wi&thorn; hir meyne,</L>
<L>a-pon &thorn;e friday efterwarde<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>ofter|warde</I>.</NOTE>,</L>
<L>of pardoun for to serue hir part;</L>
<L>&thorn;e clergi on &thorn;e seterday,</L>
<L N="268">&thorn;at kepers ware of cristen lay;</L>
<L>wi&thorn;-outen case &thorn;er daies &thorn;re</L>
<L>&thorn;is cros was &thorn;en, and man mote se;</L>
<L>&para; and hit was talde of mani man,</L>
<L N="272">at a licour &thorn;er-of ranne,</L>
<L>&thorn;at wi&thorn; betinge was bote of bale,</L>
<L>and sekenes diuers to make ham hale;</L>
<L>a vessel, &thorn;at hit ware no&yogh;t tint,</L>
<L N="276">stode vnder &thorn;at licour for to hint,</L>
<L>for to dele vn-to &thorn;e vnfere,</L>
<L>to sende ouer al &thorn;e cuntree sere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;E grace of god is grete and gode,</L>
<L N="280">&thorn;at giuis vs ensaumple of &thorn;e rode;
<PB REF="00000148.tif" N="116"></L>
<L>ma mi&yogh;tes has our lorde wro&yogh;t</L>
<L>&thorn;en ani man mai &thorn;ink in &thorn;o&yogh;t:</L>
<L>bot man of trau&thorn; is squa vnsely,</L>
<L N="284">&thorn;ai traw no&yogh;t bot &thorn;ai se wi&thorn; ey;</L>
<L>and &thorn;at vnne&thorn;is wil &thorn;ai traw,</L>
<L>wi&thorn;-outen signe of grete vertu.</L>
<L>me &thorn;ink, if &yogh;e &thorn;e so&thorn; haue so&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="288">&thorn;at syn &thorn;e werlde was first wro&yogh;t,</L>
<L>miraclis of &thorn;e crossis mi&yogh;t</L>
<L>has oft standen in stede and ri&yogh;t,</L>
<L>ouer and vnder, ri&yogh;t and left,</L>
<L N="292">in &thorn;is compas god has al weft;</L>
<L>&para; bot-if man of him-selue be blinde,</L>
<L>vm-&thorn;ink him wele he sal hit finde,</L>
<L>&thorn;e liknes of &thorn;is tree sa trew</L>
<L N="296">was in &thorn;e alde laghe, be-for &thorn;e new,</L>
<L>and in &thorn;e new laghe alsqua sere,</L>
<L>&thorn;at sum ar gode of for to here.</L>
<L>&para; I &thorn;ink &thorn;is is &thorn;at tree of blis</L>
<L N="300">&thorn;at ri&yogh;twisnes to bundin is.</L>
<L>had adam fundin hit atte hande,</L>
<L>&thorn;ar-wi&thorn; he mu&yogh;t had life lastande;</L>
<L>&thorn;at plauntid hit is in paradis</L>
<L N="304">and dos &thorn;e dede vp for to rise.</L>
<L>&para; and adam, quen he wro&yogh;t had woghe,</L>
<L>vnder &thorn;is tree he him droghe,</L>
<L>&thorn;at did him god to resoun</L>
<L N="308">and did him hope of pardoun.</L>
<L>&thorn;e blode of abel hit crid als,</L>
<L>quen him had slaine his bro&thorn;er fals;</L>
<L>wi&thorn;-in &thorn;at cry was grete &thorn;ing hid,</L>
<L N="312">&thorn;at in &thorn;is cros now is kid.</L>
<L>and dede, for so&thorn;, had bene noe,</L>
<L>had no&yogh;t him saued &thorn;at tree.</L>
<L>of foure corners &thorn;e arche was made,</L>
<L N="316">als has &thorn;e cros of lange and brade;
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="117"></L>
<L>&thorn;e dore of &thorn;e arche a-pon &thorn;e side,</L>
<L><I>and &thorn;er</I> was ihesus wounded wide;</L>
<L>qua wil vm-&thorn;inke him in his mode</L>
<L N="320">mai finde mani takenis of &thorn;e rode.</L>
<L>&para; Our lorde gaf moises a wande</L>
<L>to wirke maistri wi&thorn; in hande;</L>
<L>sum time was hit worme, sum time &yogh;erde,</L>
<L N="324">as men I.-noghe has saide and herde</L>
<L>&thorn;at wele be takenid. &thorn;at cipres,</L>
<L>&thorn;er-of was warnis[t]<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>warms</I>.</NOTE> moises,</L>
<L>ba&thorn; in worde and in dede.</L>
<L N="328">quen israel of egipt &yogh;ede,</L>
<L>of &thorn;at blessed lambis blode,</L>
<L>a cros was made in signe of rode;</L>
<L>&thorn;a at cros had on ham drawen,<MILESTONE N="90b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="332">our lorde ham sauid as for his awen;</L>
<L>and al &thorn;a o&thorn;er ware bot tint</L>
<L>and ta&yogh;t vn-to &thorn;e angels dint.</L>
<L>&para; quen &thorn;e nedderes &thorn;at ware fel</L>
<L N="336">stanged &thorn;e folk of israel,</L>
<L>quen &thorn;ai welk in wildernes,</L>
<L>vnder &thorn;e warde of sir moyses,</L>
<L>a nedder was sette a-pon a tree,</L>
<L N="340">&thorn;at quen &thorn;e stanged mu&yogh;t se</L>
<L>&thorn;e nedder on &thorn;e tree &thorn;er hange,</L>
<L>&thorn;ai ware alle warisht of &thorn;aire stange.</L>
<L>&para; quen &thorn;ai saghe, as &thorn;ai did oft,</L>
<L N="344">moises lift his hende on loft,</L>
<L>&thorn;e quilist he helde his hende on croice,</L>
<L>ay herde his awen folk &thorn;e voice.</L>
<L>&para; quen strife was a-boute presthede,</L>
<L N="348">in &thorn;e dais a-mange &thorn;e iewes lede,</L>
<L>to xij. men ta&yogh;t &thorn;ai wandes xij.,</L>
<L>ilkan merkid his him-selue,</L>
<L>and saide quilk wande beris blome</L>
<L N="352">sulde haue &thorn;e presthede wi&thorn; dome;
<PB REF="00000150.tif" N="118"></L>
<L>&thorn;er florisht an, as &yogh;e haue herde,</L>
<L>&thorn;e cros a-pon &thorn;at ilk &yogh;erde.</L>
<L>&para; Heliseus on o&thorn;er-wise</L>
<L N="356">did a dedeman for to rise;</L>
<L>&thorn;e staf &thorn;at he a-pon him did</L>
<L>&thorn;e crosse hit bare to tak in hede.</L>
<L>&para; quen dauid fa&yogh;t againe &thorn;at etin</L>
<L N="360">has he no&yogh;t his staf for-&yogh;etin;</L>
<L>vn-to &thorn;e bataile he hit bare,</L>
<L>mu&yogh;t na kinge squorde do mare.</L>
<L>&thorn;e signe of tav. in alde lawes</L>
<L N="364">be-takenis cros in our dawes,</L>
<L>&thorn;e men at &thorn;ar wi&thorn; blessed ware</L>
<L>hit helped ham fra mis-fare;</L>
<L>tav and cros ba&thorn; ar as an,</L>
<L N="368">bot. tav has &yogh;erde a-bouen nan.</L>
<L>of croice in &thorn;e alde testament</L>
<L>was mani bisening, qua to cowde tent,</L>
<L>&para; croice is, qua-sum<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>qua|sim</I>.</NOTE> wil or nay,</L>
<L N="372">baner of hali kirk to-day;</L>
<L>man has no&yogh;t herde &thorn;at fole be lorne</L>
<L>&thorn;at hali crosse has wi&thorn; ham borne.</L>
<L>bot has be-tid, ba&thorn; now and are,</L>
<L N="376">&thorn;e lesse folk ouer-come &thorn;e mare,</L>
<L>&thorn;er croice was stad atte ani fi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>if &thorn;e dude be tane wi&thorn; ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Of cros to telle for-gete I noght,</L>
<L N="380">of cros &thorn;e formast man was wro&yogh;t,</L>
<L>of cros &thorn;e first of alle wifis;</L>
<L>of cros god bo&yogh;t our saule liuis,</L>
<L>&thorn;er-on he gaf him-self raunsoun,</L>
<L N="384">and of him-self made gunfanoun.</L>
<L>&thorn;e cros of medicine beris bote,</L>
<L>ba&thorn; in frute and als in rote;</L>
<L>in cros hit was for vs &thorn;e flour</L>
<L N="388">&thorn;at we haue &thorn;orou sa grete honour.
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="119"></L>
<L>a riche liknis ay beris hit,</L>
<L>hit is &thorn;e heued of hali writte,</L>
<L>foundement. of our clergie,</L>
<L N="392">rewle hit is of haly vie.</L>
<L>makid hit is of foure and &thorn;re,</L>
<L>now is hit talde bot for a tree;</L>
<L>nokis foure and trees &thorn;rin,</L>
<L N="396">syn &thorn;e &thorn;rid was done &thorn;er-in.</L>
<L>In trees &thorn;rin and faure parates</L>
<L>I. vnderstande &thorn;e vij. artis;</L>
<L>of iiij. and iij., qua tellis eyuen,</L>
<L N="400">he sal hit noumbre make of vij.</L>
<L>&thorn;ou do to gedder x. and ij.</L>
<L>&thorn;e laghis twin sal &thorn;ou finde squa;</L>
<L>In x. sal &thorn;ou finde &thorn;e halde,</L>
<L N="404">in tale of twa &thorn;e new is talde.</L>
<L>man has on croice his schaping knawen,</L>
<L>and he him-selfe on vij is drawen,</L>
<L>ba&thorn; in bodi and saule, I. say;</L>
<L N="408">&thorn;e bodi of element&yogh; twies tway,</L>
<L>&thorn;e saule hit has of strengthis &thorn;rin,</L>
<L>&thorn;at takin of cros &thorn;ai bere wi&thorn;-in.</L>
<L>&para; quen god &thorn;at ordeins alkin state,</L>
<L N="412">of alle in his for-&thorn;o&yogh;t he wate,</L>
<L>ferlely puruaied he an;</L>
<L>a cros of tree and no&yogh;t of stane,</L>
<L>bot &thorn;at was for to make mende</L>
<L N="416">of &thorn;e tree &thorn;at was defende:</L>
<L>his cros he has wro&yogh;t with craft,</L>
<L>hit beris schap til alkin shaft.</L>
<L>wele did moises &thorn;at hit fande,</L>
<L N="420">and dauid als &thorn;at fot &thorn;e wande,</L>
<L>and salamon &thorn;at fel hit did;</L>
<L>and ho &thorn;at hit fande, quare hit was hid,</L>
<L>elaine at squa gerne hit so&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="424">and til our note now has hit bro&yogh;t,
<PB REF="00000152.tif" N="120"></L>
<L>ho delt hit wisely as ho wilde,</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;is werlde hit is fulfilde</L>
<L>of &thorn;e name and of &thorn;e smelle,<MILESTONE N="91b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="428">for-&thorn;i is gode &thorn;er-of to telle.</L>
<L>Eline ne walde no&yogh;t for lete</L>
<L>&thorn;e naylis, in hende and fete</L>
<L>&thorn;at driuen ware; ful &yogh;orne ho so&yogh;t</L>
<L N="432">til ho ham fand, fund ho no&yogh;t,</L>
<L>a werk of ham ho wro&yogh;t ful fine</L>
<L>In bridel of king costantine;</L>
<L>was na cristal als bri&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="436">ne sa shene to mani si&yogh;t;</L>
<L>quidder-sum<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>sim</I>.</NOTE> he ferde &thorn;at sire,</L>
<L>&thorn;e bridel bri&yogh;tnes bare of fire;</L>
<L>mani &thorn;at sagh &thorn;at bridel bri&yogh;t</L>
<L N="440">turned to &thorn;e grace of goddis mi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>costantine ham bare iij. &yogh;ere,</L>
<L>quen he droghe til his endinge nere,</L>
<L>out to &thorn;e bridil he ham la&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="444">and to be side &thorn;e crois ham ta&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;at mani vertu si&thorn;en wro&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;orou mi&yogh;t of crist &thorn;at vs bo&yogh;t;</L>
<L>at costantine noble and in fraunce</L>
<L N="448">god has made mani mustraunce.</L>
<L>&para; At saint denis is his croun,</L>
<L>wi&thorn; &thorn;a nailis redy boun;</L>
<L>mani man come seke and sare</L>
<L N="452">at &thorn;aire hele had fundin &thorn;are.</L>
<L>&para; now &thorn;e crois is bro&yogh;t til ende,</L>
<L>&thorn;e crois mi&yogh;t mote vs defende;</L>
<L>qua-sum<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>sim</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;is tale can beter tende,</L>
<L N="456">for cristis loue he hit amende;</L>
<L>&thorn;is tale, que&thorn;er hit be il or gode,</L>
<L>I fande hit writen of &thorn;e rode.</L>
<L>mani tellis diuerseli,</L>
<L N="460">for &thorn;ai mai finde diuerse story,
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="121"></L>
<L>&para; &thorn;at fande &thorn;e crois he hi&yogh;t Iudas;</L>
<L>made bisshop of &thorn;e toun he was,</L>
<L>and his name was turnid &thorn;us,</L>
<L N="464">&thorn;at he was calde quiriacus:</L>
<L>&para; quen fundin was &thorn;is hali crois,</L>
<L>&thorn;e warlaghe saide on-loft with vois:&mdash;</L>
<L>"a ha Iudas! quat has &thorn;ou done,</L>
<L N="468">&thorn;ou has me greued, I warne &thorn;ee sone</L>
<L>at &thorn;ou did &thorn;at cros ki&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&thorn;ou salle rew hit mani si&thorn;e;</L>
<L>&thorn;orou hit ware mani saulis myne,</L>
<L N="472">&thorn;at I am ferde now to tyne;</L>
<L>no&yogh;t for-&thorn;i I. wil no&yogh;t nyte,</L>
<L>ful wele I sal &thorn;i dedis quite;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. <I>didis</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>a-no&thorn;er kinge gaine &thorn;e sal rise</L>
<L N="476">&thorn;at sal make &thorn;e to grise,</L>
<L>and do &thorn;e suffer sa mykil shame,</L>
<L>at &thorn;ou sal nite ihesu name;</L>
<L>and &thorn;is was saide be tirand an.</L>
<L N="480">&thorn;at quiriac was of si&thorn;en slan:</L>
<L>&para; &thorn;at findis cry quen Iudas herde,</L>
<L>neuer &thorn;e mare was he ferde,</L>
<L>bot waried he &thorn;at qui&thorn;er-wine,</L>
<L N="484">and saide, "crist &thorn;at is lorde myne,</L>
<L>he deme &thorn;e in-to helle depe,</L>
<L>euer in wellande wa to wepe."</L>
<L>&THORN;at hali crois, I of haue red,</L>
<L N="488">quar-on ihesus for vs was spred,</L>
<L>hit is our shilde and our spere,</L>
<L>againis &thorn;e feinde for to were;</L>
<L>ilk day in were we weinde</L>
<L N="492">bot &thorn;at ihesu vs grace sende,</L>
<L>&thorn;orou &thorn;e crois a-gaine &thorn;e fende</L>
<L>to be our socour at our ende.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV3>
